{"about_the_game":"<p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/3316580/extras/streaks.png?t=1732654550\" /></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>OCTOPTICOM 3D</strong>\u00a0is a major upgrade to your favorite open-ended puzzle programming game about designing and optimizing optical computing devices, featuring:</p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">3D graphics and gameplay</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">a refined user interface</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">completely rewritten simulation resolving previous bugs and issues</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">all original levels and components plus new additions</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">friend leaderboards and\u00a0histograms\u00a0tracking up to five competitive metrics</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">sandbox mode and blueprints for even more creative freedom</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">remappable controls and customizable colors, along with labels, for better accessibility</p></li></ul><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>New to OCTOPTICOM and curious what it\u2019s all about?</strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"><strong>OCTOPTICOM</strong> is an open-ended puzzle programming game where you design optical circuits using mirrors, filters, and other components to read, transform, and write sequences of colors. With over 50 levels of 'light programming' in the 3D version and extensive optimization potential, it offers countless hours of problem-solving and solution refinement. Prior knowledge of electronics or programming can be helpful, but it\u2019s not required to enjoy the game! </p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\"></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\">Want to share your feedback, influence the game\u2019s development, discuss solutions with like-minded players, or get a hint when you're stuck? Join the\u00a0<strong>Discord server</strong>!</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph